  "text": "MCAO procedure has been described in details previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, after a skin incision along the midline of the mouse neck, 90-min MCA occlusion was induced in mice using an intraluminal filament. After occlusion, mice were reperfused by suture withdrawal and then sacrificed 14 or 28 days later. Mice of the sham groups underwent the same procedure as those in the stroke groups, but without occluding the MCA.",
